						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar in the same Museum No. 90.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Tribhuvanamalla [Vikramāditya VI] 12th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This record in Kannaḍa script and Sanskrit language is very much damaged. It gives a genealogical account of the dynasty of Chālukyas of Kalyāṇa upto the reign of Tribhuvanamalladēva. It registers the grant of a village and mentions some <hi rend="italic">āchāryas</hi> of some <hi rend="italic">maṭhas</hi> as the recipients of the gifts by Svāmi-daṇḍādhipa. The gift was made at the behest of the Prince Sōmēśvara.</p>						

						<p>The date portion is very much damaged and only Chālukya Vikrama year • • • • • • <hi rend="italic">uttarāyaṇa sankrānti</hi> can be made out. The information is insufficient for verification. It is in 12th century A.D. characters.</p>						

						</summary>
